Feature Plan: Venues list redesign for UIKit VenuesVC and SwiftUI VenuesMigration

Objective
- Refresh the venues list UX for both `VenuesVC` (UIKit) and `VenuesMigration` (SwiftUI) with a cleaner expanded-list style.
- Show venues vertically, one per row.
- Show selected venue details (name + address) in bottom section without map.
- Preserve existing behaviors and navigation to `VenuesDetailsVC`.

Constraints
- Keep all existing function handlers and segue identifiers.
- No backend contract changes.
- Preserve admin/map flow behavior.
- Implement parity across both targets: UIKit + SwiftUI.

Role ownership
- Primary iOS implementation: `@ios-dev`
- Contract behavior/regression checks: `@backend-dev`
- Manual flow verification: `@testing-engineer`

Target files
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesMigration/VenuesMigration.swift`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesvc-redesign.prototype.html`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.venuesvc-redesign.specify`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.venuesvc-redesign.tasks`

High-level architecture
1. List layout refresh
   - UIKit target: keep UITableView-driven architecture.
   - SwiftUI target: implement equivalent list hierarchy in `VenuesMigration`.
   - Present one venue per line with polished spacing and typography.
2. Selection details panel
   - Keep bottom details panel region.
   - On select, display selected venue and address (no map).
   - Add explicit bottom CTA for forward navigation; CTA is enabled only after row selection.
3. Navigation continuity
   - Keep `goto_venues_details` segue on selection for normal movie flow.
   - Preserve map/admin branching and notifications (especially in SwiftUI migration modes).
4. Function preservation
   - Keep `addData`, `addLocation`, `navigateBack`, `navigateToVenue`, table delegates unchanged in behavior.
5. Stability/performance guardrails
   - Avoid duplicate UI subview creation in repeated lifecycle transitions.
   - Keep async image loading non-blocking and safe for reused cells.

Interaction behavior
- User enters VenuesVC from movie selection.
- User scrolls a vertical venue list.
- User taps a venue row to select and update bottom details panel.
- User taps bottom CTA to proceed to VenuesDetailsVC (explicit second step).
- No embedded map is shown in bottom details section.
- Same interaction model is presented in both UIKit and SwiftUI targets.

Verification strategy
- Manual visual verify: expanded-list style, one-row-per-venue vertical list.
- Manual behavior verify: details panel updates with address on selection.
- Manual flow verify: still navigates to VenuesDetailsVC.
- Manual verify: map/admin flows unchanged.
- Compile verify: no Swift errors in `VenuesVC.swift`.
- Compile verify: no Swift errors in `VenuesMigration.swift`.

Definition of done
- Speckit artifacts (`.specify`, `.plan`, `.tasks`, prototype) are complete and aligned.
- Redesign is approved as polished visual update.
- Existing VenuesVC functions and navigation contracts remain intact.
- SwiftUI VenuesMigration presents equivalent redesigned behavior for the relevant list flow.

